<item>
            <title>[SPR-722] Application listeners that are prototypes aren&apos;t auto-added when instantiated</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-722</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I use lookup-method to get at a prototype that is a ApplicationListener, the listener instance isn&apos;t automatically added.  Actually, it may be the case &lt;em&gt;no prototype&lt;/em&gt; listeners are added at all &amp;#8211; and I think I&apos;ve noted this before, now that I think about it.  In any case, this behaivior is confusing and inconsistent &amp;#8211; why shouldn&apos;t prototypes be treated differently than singletons?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="11159">SPR-722</key>
            <summary>Application listeners that are prototypes aren&apos;t auto-added when instantiated</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
