                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12377" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 21 Feb 2005 02:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, that&apos;s inconsistent: other special bean types like BeanFactoryPostProcessors or HandlerMappings are accepted as prototypes too. I&apos;ve changed AbstractApplicationContext to accept prototype ApplicationListeners too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of course, any of those will typically be singletons: Why should a shared special bean for the entire context have to be a prototype? It needs to be thread-safe anyway...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27347" author="matw" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2007 13:41:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this issue is still occurring in the latest spring release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prototype beans which implement ApplicationListener are not added to the application context when you issue a context.getBean() call. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Details of this problem can be found in post - &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=44522&amp;amp;highlight=ApplicationContextAware&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=44522&amp;amp;highlight=ApplicationContextAware&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mat&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
